      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="Y47C01S1" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">He had many useful rules which he threw into rhime for the more easy recollection of them. One of them I remember was a direction to those who ride together through the water.</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-line-1"> When thro' the water you do ride,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-Y47C01S1-line-2"> Keep very close, or very wide.Y47C01S1   </l></lg></div>
